HB90 Enrolled
1 Enrolled, An Act,
2 To propose an amendment to the Constitution of Alabama
3 of 2022, relating to St. Clair County; to allow mayors of
4 municipalities in the county to participate in the Employees'
5 Retirement System of Alabama under certain conditions.
6 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
7 Section 1. The following amendment to the Constitution
8 of Alabama of 2022, is proposed:
9 PROPOSED AMENDMENT
10 In St. Clair County, the mayor of a municipality that
11 participates in the Employees' Retirement System of Alabama
12 may participate in the retirement system upon the same terms
13 and conditions as may be specified by law for any other
14 employee in the same retirement system. A mayor holding office
15 at the time of ratification of this amendment shall be
16 eligible to purchase service credit in the Employees'
17 Retirement System of Alabama for the time the official has
18 served in that office. No person may participate in both a
19 supernumerary program and the Employees' Retirement System of
20 Alabama based on the same service.
21 Upon ratification of this constitutional amendment, the
22 Code Commissioner shall number and place this amendment as
23 appropriate in the constitution omitting this instructional
24 paragraph and may make the following nonsubstantive revisions:
25 change capitalization, hierarchy, spelling, and punctuation
26 for purposes of style and uniformity; correct manifest
27 grammatical, clerical, and typographical errors; revise
Page 1

grammatical, clerical, and typographical errors; revise
HB90 Enrolled
28 internal or external citations and cross-references; harmonize
29 language; and translate effective dates.
30 END PROPOSED AMENDMENT
31 Section 2. An election upon the proposed amendment
32 shall be held in accordance with Sections 284, 284.01, and 285
33 of the Constitution of Alabama of 2022, and the election laws
34 of this state. The appropriate election official shall assign
35 a ballot number for the proposed constitutional amendment on
36 the election ballot and shall set forth the following
37 description of the substance or subject matter of the proposed
38 constitutional amendment:
39 "Relating to St. Clair County, proposing an amendment
40 to the Constitution of Alabama of 2022, to allow mayors to
41 participate in the Employees' Retirement System of Alabama
42 under certain conditions.
43 Proposed by Act ____."
44 This description shall be followed by the following
45 language:
46 "Yes( ) No( )."
47 Section 3. The proposed amendment shall become valid as
48 part of the Constitution of Alabama of 2022, when approved by
49 a majority of the qualified electors voting thereon.
